Package calc

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Calculator
    This interface is so that both the reverse polish calculator and the infix calculator have an evaluate method.
    Operator
    This interface is for the operators of the calculate, so they all implement the calculate method.
    TreeNode
    This interface is to implement a tree for the expression.
    Visitor
    This interface is to implement the visitor design pattern..
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalcModel
    This class is the model of the entire calculator.
    CalcVisitor
    This class implements the visitor, so it can span a tree to evaluate an expression.
    Divide
    This class implements the operator interface, so the calculate function can return the answer of x / y.
    Entry
    This class will be used to store the users input, to be used within the Stack class.
    InFixCalc
    This class implements the calculator interface.
    Multiply
    This class implements the operator interface, so that the calculate method returns the answer to x * y.
    NumberNode
    This class implements the TreeNode so numbers can be stored.
    OperatorNode
    This class will implement to the TreeNode for operators.
    OperatorStack
    This class is a facade of the Stack class for the use of symbols.
    Plus
    This class implements the operator interface to create a addition class.
    RevPolishCalc
    This class implements the calculator for the purpose of evaluating the calculation if it is written in reverse polish.
    Stack
    This is the class that is used to store entries so they can be retrieved in the correct order.
    Subtract
    This class implements the operator interface, so that the calculate method returns the subtraction between two numbers.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    EntryType
    This is list of possible types of the entry.
    Symbol
    This is the list of possible symbols.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BadEntryTypeException
    This is the exception that is thrown when the user entered a invalid type.
    EmptyStackException
    This is the exception that is thrown when the stack contains 0 elements.
    InvalidExpressionException
    This exception is thrown when the user inputs a invalid expression.
